<!-- INSTRUCTIONS SECTION -->
<center><h2><u><font color="#8b0000">Cooking Instructions</font></u></h2></center>

<table width="85%" align="center" border="1" cellpadding="10" bgcolor="#fffaf0" bordercolor="#deb887">
<tr><td>
    <ol type="1">
        <li>In a pan, saut√© <b>garlic</b>, <b>onion</b>, and <b>ginger</b> until aromatic.</li>
        <li>Add <strong>pork belly</strong> and cook until it turns light brown.</li>
        <li>Stir in <mark>shrimp paste</mark> and cook for about 3 minutes.</li>
        <li>Pour the <em>coconut milk</em> and simmer until the pork becomes tender.</li>
        <li>Add <b>green chilies</b> and let it simmer until the sauce thickens.</li>
        <li>Season with <small>salt</small> and <small>pepper</small> to taste.</li>
        <li>For extra heat, mix in <font color="red"><b>red chili peppers</b></font>.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with <strong>steamed rice</strong> ‚Äî enjoy the Bicolano flavor!</li>
    </ol>
</td></tr>
</table>

